outputs.output_descr:
The Project supports Solomon Islands efforts towards achievement of the Millennium Development Goals (MDGs) through MDG based planning and costing, targeted capacity building, and updating of the National MDGs Report.

The project is implemented in 3 stages namely: scoping, initiating and maturing. It will focus on the review/development of national development planning and budgetary processes and on strengthening sector strategies; prioritization of activities and budget allocation; better linking of aid coordination and management with national priorities; and strengthening information systems for monitoring the effectiveness of national planning and budget implementation at the national, sectoral and local levels. The project also supports improvements in monitoring and reporting.

The project is led by the Solomon Islands Government and facilitated by UNDP in coordination with other organizations of the United Nations System.

The project is organized under the following four key activities:

i)	MDGI Project preparation and Baseline Assessment undertaken;
ii)	MDGs Needs Assessment and Costing undertaken;
iii)	MDGs mainstreamed into national systems;
iv)	MDG Progress Reports finalized.
